All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
App
The App class is the entry point for the hotel management system application.
CheckInCommand
The CheckInCommand class represents the command to check a guest into a room.
CheckOutCommand
The CheckOutCommand class represents the command to check a guest out of a room.
Command
The Command class is an abstract base class for all command classes in the system.
CSVReader
The CSVReader class provides functionality for reading room and hotel data from a CSV file and converting it into Hotel and Room objects.
CSVWriter
The CSVWriter class provides methods for writing hotel room data into a CSV file.
HelpCommand
The HelpCommand class represents the command that displays a list of available commands to the user.
Hotel
The Hotel class represents a hotel containing rooms.
InvalidCommand
The InvalidCommand class represents the command that is executed when an invalid command is entered by the user.
ListCommand
The ListCommand class is used to display a list of all rooms in the hotel along with their availability, guest data, and check-in/check-out dates.
Map<K,V>
The Map interface defines the structure and methods for a key-value storage collection, where each key is associated with a value.
MyMap<K,V>
This class implements a simple map using two lists: one for keys and one for values.
PricesCommand
The PricesCommand class is used to display the prices of all rooms in the hotel.
Room
The Room class represents a hotel room that can be rented by guests.
RoomAvailable
The RoomAvailable class represents an exception thrown when trying to perform an operation on a room that is available (not checked in).
RoomNotAvailable
The RoomNotAvailable class represents an exception thrown when trying to perform an operation on a room that is not available (already checked in).
RoomNotExist
The RoomNotExist class represents an exception thrown when trying to access a room that does not exist.
SaveCommand
The SaveCommand class is responsible for saving the current hotel data to a CSV file.
ViewCommand
The ViewCommand class is responsible for displaying detailed information about a specific room in the hotel.
WrongInput
The WrongInput class represents an exception thrown when an invalid input is entered.
